  "riddle": "Here is the rewritten riddle:\n\n1. Seek the township in LaSalle County, Illinois, known for its agricultural roots; there find how many residents were recorded in the 2020 census, then follow the link on that page to the neighboring township whose name echoes an ancient Roman family.\n\n2. There exists a page for that neighboring township; on it convert 574 meters into yards and report the whole-yard total (discard any fractional yard), then click the link to the nearby township whose name evokes a task or assignment to continue.\n\n3. What whole-yard figure results when you perform the same 574‑metre-to‑yards conversion on that \"task\"-named township page, again discarding any fractional part?\n\n4. The article whose name suggests a mission holds your next instruction: take the whole-yard number you just found and repeatedly sum its digits until only a single digit remains — what is that final digit?\n\n5. The ledger now demands a final tally: compute (clue 1 + clue 2 + clue 3 + clue 4) modulo 10 and give the result as a single digit (0–9).",
